# sumo-otel-local project config — copy to .sumo-otel-local.env and edit.
#
# This file is SOURCED by sumo-otel-local.sh (when present in the working directory),
# so it is plain shell: KEY=value, one per line, no spaces around '='. Values set here
# are applied for the run (loaded with `set -a`), so you can avoid re-answering prompts.
# To ignore this file for a single run, set SUMO_CONFIG_FILE=/dev/null (or point it at
# another path to use a different config).
#
# Copy and uncomment what you need:

# Container runtime: docker or podman (skips the "which runtime?" prompt when both exist).
# CONTAINER_RUNTIME=docker

# KinD cluster name (default: sumo). Used by create, status, and teardown.
# CLUSTER_NAME=sumo

# Pinned sumologic/sumologic Helm chart version (skips the version picker).
# SUMO_CHART_VERSION=5.2.0

# Helm values file passed to install/output (default: values.yaml if present).
# HELM_VALUES=examples/metrics_interval.yaml

# Podman machine minimums (MiB / vCPUs).
# MIN_MEM_MB=18432
# MIN_CPU=4

# Run unattended (assume yes, use defaults). Equivalent to -y. Note: destructive
# teardown (-u/-p) still requires the explicit --force flag even with this set.
# ASSUME_YES=yes

# NOT configurable here for safety: --force (destructive auto-confirm) is flag-only,
# and Sumo credentials must come from secret storage or SUMOLOGIC_ACCESS_ID/KEY.
